This paper deals with the evaluation of generative models, specifically GANs, using neural network divergences. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of these metrics for measuring diversity and generalization, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and validation of the proposed metric, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
